---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Gardner Denley | Web Design Case Study | Adam Barnes"
  description="Bespoke WordPress website for Gardner Denley, Cambridge's prime property buying agency. Creative direction by David Porter."
  canonical="https://www.adambarnes.biz/case-study-gardner-denley.html"
  ogImage="https://www.adambarnes.biz/assets/og-image.jpg"
  ogType="article"
  bodyClass="page-webdesign"
  active="web-design"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "CreativeWork",
    "name": "Gardner Denley Website",
    "url": "https://gardnerdenley.com",
    "creator": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Adam Barnes",
      "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz"
    },
    "description": "Bespoke WordPress website for Gardner Denley, Cambridge's prime residential property buying agency.",
    "keywords": [
      "WordPress",
      "Web Design",
      "Elementor",
      "CSS",
      "Property",
      "Cambridge"
    ]
  }
  </script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 1,
        "name": "Home",
        "item": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/"
      },
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 2,
        "name": "Web Design",
        "item": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/web-design.html"
      },
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": 3,
        "name": "Gardner Denley",
        "item": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/case-study-gardner-denley.html"
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Gardner Denley — Web Design Case Study",
    "description": "Bespoke WordPress website for Gardner Denley, Cambridge's prime property buying agency. Creative direction by David Porter.",
    "about": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Gardner Denley",
        "url": "https://gardnerdenley.com"
    },
    "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz/case-study-gardner-denley.html",
    "author": {
        "@type": "Person",
        "name": "Adam Barnes",
        "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz"
    },
    "publisher": {
        "@type": "Person",
        "name": "Adam Barnes",
        "url": "https://www.adambarnes.biz"
    },
    "datePublished": "2026-04-01",
    "dateModified": "2026-04-22"
}
  </script>
  </Fragment>

<main>

    <!-- Page header -->
    <header class="section-header webdesign-header cs-header">
      <div class="cs-header-text">
        <h1 class="section-title">
          <span>Gardner</span>
          <span class="accent">Denley</span>
          <span class="by-line">by Adam</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="section-intro">
          <span class="intro-lead">Cambridge's prime property buying agency.</span>
          A bespoke WordPress build for a niche consultancy operating at the top end of the residential market, where the digital presence needs to match the properties it represents.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-header-logo" aria-hidden="true">
        <img src="assets/logos/gardnerdenley.svg" alt="">
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Case study body -->
    <section class="cs-body reveal" aria-label="Case study detail">
      <div class="cs-body-inner">

        <!-- Meta strip -->
        <div class="cs-meta">
          <div class="cs-meta-item">
            <span class="cs-meta-label">Client</span>
            <span class="cs-meta-value">Gardner Denley</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-meta-item">
            <span class="cs-meta-label">Live site</span>
            <span class="cs-meta-value"><a href="https://gardnerdenley.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gardnerdenley.com</a></span>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-meta-item">
            <span class="cs-meta-label">Creative direction</span>
            <span class="cs-meta-value">David Porter</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-meta-item">
            <span class="cs-meta-label">Services</span>
            <span class="cs-meta-value">Web Design · WordPress · Elementor · CSS</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Narrative -->
        <div class="cs-copy">
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The brief</h2>
            <p>Gardner Denley operates at the top end of the Cambridge residential market. Their clients expect clarity, discretion and confidence from the first interaction.</p>
            <p>The existing website didn't reflect that. It lacked structure, presence and the authority needed to match the properties and clients they deal with. The new site needed to feel controlled, considered and credible from the first glance.</p>

            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The work</h2>
            <p>Creative direction came from David Porter, a consultant creative director with 40 years across TV, press and branding, including Leo Burnett London. Working together from the initial client meetings through to the finished site meant David's creative thinking could be shaped by what Elementor could genuinely deliver, with custom CSS used to push beyond its limits where needed.</p>
            <p>A custom WordPress build using Elementor formed the foundation, with bespoke CSS throughout to remove template constraints and give precise control over layout and behaviour.</p>
            <p>Every decision was deliberate:</p>
            <ul class="cs-list">
              <li>Typography chosen to carry weight without excess</li>
              <li>Spacing used to create pace and clarity</li>
              <li>Navigation simplified to reduce friction</li>
              <li>Content hierarchy structured to guide rather than decorate</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For a look at the same Elementor foundation taken in a very different direction, see the <a href="case-study-uk-director-magazine.html">UK Director Magazine case study</a>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-copy-col">
            <h2 class="cs-copy-heading">The outcome</h2>
            <p>The site works as a key entry point for new relationships, reinforcing credibility before any direct contact is made. The team can update content and refine messaging without friction, keeping the site current without ongoing redevelopment.</p>
            <p>When someone lands on the site, the question of whether Gardner Denley operates at the right level is answered within seconds.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Screenshots -->
    <section class="cs-screenshots reveal" aria-label="Project screenshots">
      <figure class="cs-screenshot">
        <!-- Replace with: assets/images/gardner-denley-1.jpg -->
        <img src="assets/images/gardner-denley-1.webp" alt="Gardner Denley website, homepage" class="cs-screenshot-img" loading="lazy">
        <figcaption>Homepage, leading with the brand</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="cs-screenshot">
        <!-- Replace with: assets/images/gardner-denley-2.jpg -->
        <img src="assets/images/gardner-denley-2.webp" alt="Gardner Denley website, services page" class="cs-screenshot-img" loading="lazy">
        <figcaption>Services, clear, considered structure</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <!-- Back link + CTA -->
    <div class="cs-footer-nav reveal">
      <a href="web-design.html" class="cs-back-link">← Back to Web Design</a>
      <a href="contact.html" class="btn">Start a project</a>
    </div>

  </main>
</Base>
